I would really recommend these considering its great price. :) READ MORE

name: JBL T250SI Headphone
content:
Just got these headphones yesterday and trust me i am not lying a bit, these are really awesome. I was very scared because of those negative reviews and stuff and comparisons to skullcandy, but after actually using this, i am so surprised. All those negative ratings are wrong or maybe they got faulty product. Here are some pros and cons for it :-
PROS-
1. Awesome bass. Loved it. Those who said that bass is not satisfactory and dont go for it if u are a music lover, please ignore. The bass is very pure and will suit almost anyone. I am a bass lover and mainly listen to EDM songs, and hearing EDM in JBL is just a charm :)
2.Nice treble alongside with the bass. No complaints in this price range.
3.some people reviewed that headphone loudness aint enough, dude it matters with what phone you are using. I am using redmi 4 and applied 'over the ear' settings in music options, and these headphones performance just boosted like hell.
4. Long wire cable, no issues.
5. That orange JBL logo looks quite awesome with the black background and are veryy stylish.
6. Comfort. The upper portion is having soft cushion for added comfort.
CONS-
1. Wires are thin, need to take care or you may damage them easily.
2. not foldable guys. U cant carry it in your bag or else it will break.
3. Yes it pains a little in the ear if u are using continuously for 2-3 hours. But thats not a major problem at all.
Thats it guys, couldnt find any other cons lol. Maybe my review helped you. Without thinking go for it and thank me later. Cheers :) READ MORE

name: JBL T250SI Headphone
content:
So I got my JBL at a bargain of Rs. 799 last month even though it's cheaper right now.
The audio, clarity & bass is perfect for a budget headphone and it does not look cheap at all.

Pros:-
* Excellent audio
* Easy on your wallet
* Got it delivered in 2 days; good packaging
* Stylish
* Good ear support-covers the ear so outside noise isn't heard

Cons:-
* Even though the band is adjustable, it's too rigid and your ear hurts after maybe 30min of usage.
* It's wired so if you want it hassle-free, go for a wireless one.

On the whole, it's a well built product from JBL for every Indian.
Go for it if you don't use it for long hours. READ MORE

name: JBL T250SI Headphone
review title: Justice to the price Rs. 700-1000 and brand name
content:
let's directly talk about Pros & Cons
Pros:

1- If your are buying a premium company head phones for the first time like JBl, or Senheiser or Beats, then it is must buy for you to experience a total balance of bass and crystal clear sound in the price range mentioned in the review title.
2- The soft pad provides easiness to put over the ears and make the experience more wearable.
3- For big head size like mine, the adjustment panel does the trick and over it has all needed degree of freedom to adjust as per your convenience.

4- Look has been given a perfect care which is so stylish that will make you feel good. It is sleek, stylish and convenient to wear.
5- It can be used while travelling by proper adjusting with your head-ear sizes.
6- No un-necessary noise and when the music is on full swing, you will be lost in the world of melodies, rhythm, beats and bass.
Cons
1- If you pay for it more than Rs. 1000-1100, don't go for it for this product, as you can find some other company good same range head phones.
2- I must admit, the head phone's self volume is quite low. So be sure when you buy it, you have good volume range in the players of your mobiles or PC.
3- If you are audiophiles, you must go for entry level Sony head-phones or Sennheiser.

Test on audio Frequency:
It has worked fine from 15000 Hz till 70-80 Hz, which shows that, its frequency is quite broader and worked good at low frequency. Working at lower frequency shows, it can play low quality audios or low quality mp3s. You can do it yourself once you have it. Just go to Youtube and search for test/frequency test for head phones, you will find the tester videos.
Overall verdict: Go for it if your budget is Rs-1000-1100 (don't pay more than this for it). READ MORE
